write a puppet Xen/libxl/Xenlight module that should do the following:
- install xen
- start virtual machines (if needed)
- stop virtual machines (if status to stop, or purge)
- manage vcpu(pools)
- create config files
- set settings like save and resume

facter
- detect if dom0
- list running machine
- list availible configs
- list availible vcpu's

Use PDK (https://puppet.com/docs/puppet/6.17/create_types_and_providers_resource_api.html)

Links:
https://www.jertype.com/posts/calling-c-shared-library/
